4.2 Dark Energy: The IR Tail of the Fixed Point
The origin of Dark Energy (DE) in the QSSM is directly linked to the UV fixed point resolution of the cosmological constant problem (Chapter 2).
The observed vacuum energy (\Lambda_{obs}) is the small, positive residue left over from the RG flow as the system moves from the UV fixed point (f_4^*=0) down to the Infrared (IR) scale, which is set by the mass of the Dark Matter particle (m_{DM}).
